This paper focuses on aspect-based sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed framework involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of cross-shared units, which are a type of neural network architecture commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
